<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Basically it isnt the RTA who decides everything like that for the rathe but BoTS, Tindi and NB leadership? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The rules of rotations are decided by the guilds on the rotations.  If you want to know the rotation agreement on Arch Lich, talk to NB, Tindi, or BotS... not RTA.  If you want to know the rotation agreement on Trakanon, talk to NB, LoL, TL, VoF, CoN, ED, VoLS, FS, FK, EotF, LoM, and S4H.  For Zlandicar, talk to NB, LoL, VoF, FK, TL, HE, CB, LoM, CoN, and SoY.  For other mobs, look at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.jakefitch.com/rta/Rotations.asp">www.jakefitch.com/rta/Rotations.asp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> which is where I cut and pasted those lists from.  The RTA is a collection of committees I guess...  not a single committee.<br>
<br>
I can tell you a lot of the original agreements on mobs but I couldn't tell you the latest agreements on several (like Trakanon or Severilous or Zlandicar) because we aren't active participants of those rotations anymore.  They may have changed the rules since we were in those rotations. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrommofbots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gromm of BotS</A> at: 9/16/02 7:19:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugranitfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Granitfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/16/02 10:21:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=36>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ToVN Rotation agreement/rules</span><hr size=1> Nyca as all know CE is not even close to being able to try these mobs.  The reason I took my stance on this was because it was brought up and now seemed like the best time to address this.  In a month or 2 CE might be able to do these 2 mobs, other guilds are ready now.<br>
